YELLOW FEVER - AMERICAS (09): BRAZIL (GOIAS) MONKEY, FATAL
**********************************************************
A ProMED-mail post
http://www.promedmail.org
ProMED-mail is a program of the
International Society for Infectious Diseases
http://www.isid.org

Date: Fri 30 Oct 2020
Source: G1 [in Portuguese, trans. Mod.TY, edited]
https://g1.globo.com/go/goias/noticia/2020/10/30/sobe-para-sete-o-numero-de-macacos-mortos-por-febre-amarela-em-menos-de-um-mes-em-goias.ghtml


The number of monkeys dead of yellow fever in Goias has risen to 7 in one month. The Epidemiological Secretariat [SES] stated that just in Goiania, 200 000 adults and 20 000 children still need to receive doses of the vaccine. Immunization is free and can be done at health centers. [A surprising number for a municipality where vaccination has been recommended for years. - Mod.RNA]

State superintendent of health surveillance, Fluvia Amorim, warns of the risk of virus circulation, which had not appeared in the state for 3 years.

"The death of the monkeys works as a warning to the entire population," said the superintendent. "It means that the virus has circulated again. The last cycle we had started in 2015 and ended in 2017. It is a preventable disease that has a vaccine, and there is no reason why people put themselves at risk."

According to the State Secretariat of Health (SES), until Thursday [29 Oct 2020], there was a record of the death of monkeys by the virus in 4 cities. The 1st 4 deaths were confirmed on 20 Oct [2020]. The secretary also points out that the animal is not a [direct] transmitter of the disease.

Cities that have registered monkeys dead of the disease [What species? In urban or forested areas? - Mod.RNA]:
- Goiania: 4
- Abadia de Goias: 1
- Aragoiania: 1
- Aparecida de Goiania: 1

In Goias, vaccination coverage for yellow fever in children under one year of age is 64% of the target, according to the SES. The superintendent explains that the 1st dose of vaccine is given at 9 months of age and a booster dose at 4 years of age. The vaccine can be found at health centers and is free. After taking both doses, the person is immune for life.

"Above 5 years, the person must have at least one dose registered on the [vaccination] card," explains Fluvia. "Whoever is not in this situation, the advice is to look for a vaccination post as soon as possible and get vaccinated."

According to the Ministry of Health, the most common symptoms of yellow fever are fever, body pain, weakness, diarrhea, and vomiting. The case fatality rate of the disease reaches 40%.

[Byline: Guilherme Rodrigues]

